<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="Slope" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Slope</title>
    <p>
        In this section, we will learn how to calculate and interpret the slope of a line.
    </p>

    <definition xml:id="SlopeDefinition">
        <statement>
            <p>
                The <term>Slope</term> between two points <m>(x_1, y_1)</m> and <m>(x_2, y_2)</m> is given by the formula:
                <me>
                    m = \frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}
                </me>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>


